==Old English==

===Etymology===
Common Germanic: cognate with Old Saxon [[skakan]], Old Norse [[skaka]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'ʃacan/

===Intransitive Verb===
'''scacan''' (Class VI strong)
# to [[pass]] or [[depart]]
# to [[quiver]] or [[vibrate]]

===Transitive Verb===
'''scacan''' (Class VI strong)
# to [[flourish]] or [[wave]] (an object)
# to cause something to [[quiver]] or [[flutter]]

===Descendents===
Modern English [[shake]]

